    176 Usage: jsonic <args> [<source-text>]*
    177
    178 where
    179 <source-text> is the source text to be parsed into JSON.
    180 If omitted, the source text is read from STDIN. If multiple source texts

    183

    193

    195 -m <meta=value> can be a dotted path (see option example).
    196
    197 --plugin <require> Load a plugin, where <require> is the plugin module
    198 -p <require> reference (name or path).
